Furthermore, it may be viewed as a [[facetting|facetted]] [[dodecahedron]]: the [[pentagon]]al faces may be inscribed within the dodecahedron's pentagons. Its [[Dual polyhedron|dual]], the [[medial triambic icosahedron]], is a [[stellation]] of the [[icosahedron]].

It is topologically equivalent to a quotient space of the [[hyperbolic geometry|hyperbolic]] [[order-6 pentagonal tiling]], by distorting the [[pentagram]]s back into regular [[pentagon]]s. As such, it is a [[regular polyhedron]] of index two:<ref>[http://homepages.wmich.edu/~drichter/regularpolyhedra.htm The Regular Polyhedra (of index two)], David A. Richter</ref>

