=== Great rhombic triacontahedron===
{{Uniform polyhedra db|Uniform dual polyhedron stat table|gID}}
The [[Dual polyhedron|dual]] of the great icosidodecahedron is the '''[[great rhombic triacontahedron]]'''; it is nonconvex, [[Isohedral figure|isohedral]] and [[isotoxal]].  It has 30 intersecting [[rhombus|rhombic]] faces. It can also be called the great stellated triacontahedron.

The great rhombic triacontahedron can be constructed by expanding the size of the faces of a [[rhombic triacontahedron]] by a factor of <math>\varphi^3 = 1+2\varphi\! = 2+\sqrt{5}</math>, where <math>\varphi\!</math> is the [[golden ratio]].

