In [[geometry]], the '''small dodecicosidodecahedron''' is a [[nonconvex uniform polyhedron]], indexed as U<sub>33</sub>.  Its [[vertex figure]] is a [[quadrilateral#More quadrilaterals|crossed quadrilateral]].

==Related polyhedra==
It shares its [[vertex arrangement]] with the [[small stellated truncated dodecahedron]] and the [[Polyhedron compound#Uniform compounds|uniform compounds]] of [[compound of six pentagrammic prisms|6]] or [[compound of twelve pentagrammic prisms|12 pentagrammic prisms]]. It additionally shares its [[edge arrangement]] with the [[rhombicosidodecahedron]] (having the triangular and pentagonal faces in common), and with the [[small rhombidodecahedron]] (having the decagonal faces in common).

